                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 190.) I took the prisoner, and found on him eight shillings and 2 3/4 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and some papers and books—the pro<lb></lb>secutor said he lost eight shillings and 4 3/4 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he tried to keep his money back, and gave me a shilling, but I found a purse on him, containing seven shillings—he had got the purse up the sleeve of his shirt—the prosecutor immediately identified this shilling, as being chafed and marked—the prisoner had a quan<lb></lb>tity of bread.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I don't know anything about it.</p>
